This paper discusses robotic manipulation and learning from demonstration, which are core topics in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a new approach to learning that integrates multiple forms of skill acquisition, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sophisticated contact control, which is a topic of interest in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for new possibilities in human-robot interaction, which is a topic of interest in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
